Dialogue: 10,0:00:12.24,0:00:14.33,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I don't see any of the infants.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.33,0:00:16.12,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We're leaving 'em behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:17.36,0:00:21.13,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I thought about what you were telling me before.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:22.07,0:00:23.37,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I reconsidered.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:24.03,0:00:27.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We've got everyone five and above on board.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:27.86,0:00:31.33,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They were obviously shocked, \Nbut I think it'll work out.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:31.33,0:00:33.40,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We're moving on to the next \Nstages of their training, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.40,0:00:34.39,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.93,0:00:36.93,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,So, what now?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:36.93,0:00:39.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Do we tell the infants too?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.41,0:00:42.42,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Think they'll believe us?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.42,0:00:45.98,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,And if they do, can they keep the plan a secret?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.98,0:00:47.78,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,That's not all.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:48.43,0:00:50.85,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Can we really take them along?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.85,0:00:51.53,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.04,0:00:55.79,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It's not that I don't believe in Norman's plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:56.21,0:01:01.29,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But there's the chasm, \Nit'll be winter, and Norman's gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.82,0:01:05.98,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even after we escape, we'll have to expect \Nthe unexpected out in the wild.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.98,0:01:11.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I know this is really late,\N but I feel like Ray made a good point.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.55,0:01:12.80,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You mean...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.52,0:01:16.18,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We mustn't lead them to their deaths\N by getting them out of here.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:16.18,0:01:18.68,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But if we leave them behind, they'll be shipped out.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.68,0:01:20.11,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,100)}I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:20.11,0:01:22.10,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,0)}I know...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.77,0:01:29.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We really can't leave 'em behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.76,0:01:32.68,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Ray's right,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.68,0:01:34.30,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,and so are you, Gilda.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.60,0:01:39.37,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm done with seeing people get shipped out.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.90,0:01:43.37,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.37,0:01:45.63,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We'll take our entire family along.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.44,0:01:47.99,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Let's run away, all of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.66,0:01:51.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,"All of us"?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.51,0:01:53.01,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.01,0:01:55.60,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Well, uh,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.47,0:01:58.64,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,what about the kids in the other plants?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.89,0:02:03.14,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Is it okay for us to just leave them?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.13,0:02:08.97,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We've never met them, \Nbut they're right here, aren't they?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.97,0:02:13.66,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Families just like ours that live\N in ignorance, like we did?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.91,0:02:23.23,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry! Forget it!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.57,0:02:26.31,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,What do we do, Emma?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.68,0:02:32.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I agree, we can't just ignore 'em.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.25,0:02:45.49,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Get Phil for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.44,0:02:48.50,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.50,0:02:51.69,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I need to tell you something \Nabout this House and Mom.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.92,0:02:57.20,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.58,0:02:58.83,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,So it was like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.58,0:03:09.20,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I've been wondering about that "harvest"\N the Sister mentioned during tag.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.20,0:03:12.81,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I even saw her checking Ray's drawer.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.81,0:03:13.59,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,And you...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.59,0:03:18.09,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,The day Norman left, you looked afraid of Mom.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.85,0:03:21.32,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I thought it was weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.30,0:03:26.63,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.81,0:03:29.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Norman got harvested.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.97,0:03:33.22,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Conny
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.47,0:03:35.91,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,and everyone else, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.57,0:03:38.61,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,That's why you...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.12,0:03:41.99,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Phil...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.62,0:03:48.25,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We won't take 'em just yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.83,0:03:53.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}None of the younger kids besides Phil \Nknow about the House's secret or the fire.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.88,0:03:55.63,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I've asked him to handle all that.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.59,0:04:00.05,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Phil, listen up.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.53,0:04:02.81,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Right now, I dunno what decision to make.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.63,0:04:08.14,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Take everyone, even the toddlers,\N or leave everyone below the age of five behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.15,0:04:12.89,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Only the kids who are six or older get harvested.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.89,0:04:18.15,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even the oldest of the infants, Manya,\N has a year and a half left still.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.70,0:04:21.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, the House'll lose fifteen older kids.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.51,0:04:26.66,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Since they value quality over quantity, \Nthey'll slow down the shipments.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.28,0:04:33.67,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It'll be harder for 'em to kill older kids\N who could become high-quality produce.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.91,0:04:41.18,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Not just that, you and the five other \Nfour-year-olds have decent scores.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.56,0:04:45.31,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I think you've got at least another two years or so.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.77,0:04:48.02,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma, are you saying...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.02,0:04:50.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I can wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.90,0:04:52.79,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,So leave me behind!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.11,0:04:57.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm not leaving 'em to die.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.55,0:05:00.05,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We'll be back here before their time comes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.05,0:05:01.28,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,And when we return,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.96,0:05:07.02,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}we'll take Phil and the rest,\N and all the kids from the other four plants.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.41,0:05:10.76,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Phil, where are the others?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.29,0:05:15.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.29,0:05:34.69,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.69,0:05:37.91,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Where are Emma and the others?\N Aren't they with you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.91,0:05:39.19,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I'll go get them right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.40,0:05:43.00,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I promise I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.00,0:05:45.45,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Be good kids and don't move from here, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.20,0:05:53.46,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,This is 73584 from Plant 3!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.93,0:05:56.21,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We have an escape! Sound the alarm!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.82,0:06:01.71,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,That was sooner than expected.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.93,0:06:04.22,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.22,0:06:05.63,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We're still pretty far from the bridge.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.22,0:06:08.20,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Attention all units.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.20,0:06:10.08,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Urgent message from Plant 3.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.08,0:06:13.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Fifteen kids are making an escape following the fire.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.17,0:06:15.16,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Two of them are top-quality.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.16,0:06:18.23,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,As such, we shall enter the highest alert mode.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.23,0:06:20.36,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You may kill anyone other than the top-quality pair.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.12,0:06:24.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But make sure there is nary\N a scratch on any of their heads.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.88,0:06:27.75,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Capture them as soon as they're located.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.74,0:06:30.75,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare let them escape!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.75,0:06:33.25,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Run away if you can,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.81,0:06:34.61,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.18,0:06:40.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We'll cross the chasm from here.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.47,0:06:42.11,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.77,0:06:43.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Cross the chasm?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.17,0:06:46.26,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But back then, Norman said...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.86,0:06:48.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,The bridge is the only way out.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.00,0:06:51.52,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Or so they'd like you to think.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.25,0:06:54.97,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,That trying to cross the chasm would be too risky.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.97,0:06:59.02,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That's why you'll ignore \Nthe bridge and do exactly that.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.38,0:07:02.53,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I checked both the distance to \Nthe other side and the terrain there.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.05,0:07:05.71,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It's risky, but there {\i1}is{\i0} one spot that looks promising.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.52,0:07:10.28,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, you still have two months to prepare.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.88,0:07:14.79,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Relax.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.26,0:07:17.37,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We trained like crazy for this.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.12,0:07:19.29,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,"Trained"?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.82,0:07:50.98,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Nat!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.98,0:07:51.84,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,On it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.08,0:07:58.58,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.22,0:08:01.25,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.25,0:08:05.00,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,This'll work so long as we get one person across.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.00,0:08:05.84,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.35,0:08:17.99,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,He did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.99,0:08:20.48,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Okay! It's our turn now!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.55,0:08:25.23,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,One, two...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.49,0:08:32.24,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.35,0:08:37.50,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,All good here!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.50,0:08:40.24,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Smell ya later, Ray!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.83,0:08:49.93,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You guys...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.88,0:08:53.05,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.58,0:09:01.14,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,When did you all...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.78,0:09:04.44,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.45,0:09:18.96,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Wipe that smug look off your face.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.96,0:09:22.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, I got you hook, line, and sinker!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.17,0:09:25.67,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"I'll show you something good,\N so shut up and come with," eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.26,0:09:28.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I was right, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.24,0:09:30.42,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.76,0:09:33.44,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,This is something we thought we would never see.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.01,0:09:34.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.35,0:09:38.89,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I thought getting everyone out was impossible.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.53,0:09:42.69,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I looked down on them all as dead weight.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.40,0:09:44.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I hesitated too.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.59,0:09:49.69,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But I was able to decide in the end thanks to Emma.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.36,0:09:53.20,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Only Emma can make everyone\N believe in and follow her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.44,0:09:56.81,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,She's rash and reckless,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.81,0:09:58.20,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,but unwavering.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.85,0:10:01.69,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Someone who'd choose everyone\N without a moment's thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.52,0:10:07.10,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You don't have to give up, Ray.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.91,0:10:13.44,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Found them?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.44,0:10:14.83,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,No! Keep searching!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.33,0:10:17.39,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Have they not reached the bridge?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.39,0:10:18.10,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.52,0:10:20.58,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Check the bushes! Find them!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.58,0:10:21.56,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.10,0:10:23.98,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.40,0:10:26.90,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Five more!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.88,0:10:30.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma, help.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.95,0:10:34.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,M-My hands are shaking... Sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.51,0:10:36.87,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Thinking about the chasm scared me!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.17,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,What if I fall?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.17,0:10:42.41,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,F-Fall?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.49,0:11:02.47,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Jemima.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.09,0:11:04.70,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,We can cross together.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.70,0:11:05.96,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Ray?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.96,0:11:06.85,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Emma.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.85,0:11:09.83,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We still have the rope we used \Nto pull everyone up the wall, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.83,0:11:11.43,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.43,0:11:14.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Use it to tie Jemima to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.53,0:11:17.27,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Do you know how to cross?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.27,0:11:18.68,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I picked it up from watching them.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.49,0:11:20.90,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,How about you guys?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.90,0:11:22.96,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna say you can't do it, are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.19,0:11:26.95,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,R-R-Relax!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.95,0:11:28.83,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,W-W-We're all good!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.20,0:11:31.59,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Well said.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.93,0:11:34.09,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Jemima.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.82,0:11:54.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Look, Jemima. We're here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.57,0:12:06.97,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I lose, Norman.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.59,0:12:19.99,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Last one!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.99,0:12:21.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Come on, Emma!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.57,0:12:55.83,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Grace Field House.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.50,0:13:02.89,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, our beloved home.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.49,0:13:06.89,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Mom.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.53,0:13:09.26,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Don't go, Emma...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.47,0:13:12.94,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,My dear children!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.03,0:14:38.32,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Isabella?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.95,0:14:41.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Don't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.90,0:14:44.36,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.36,0:14:48.19,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I heard this beautiful music while I was\N up in the tree, so I had to come see.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.99,0:14:50.67,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Did you compose that, Leslie?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.65,0:14:52.61,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.61,0:14:54.24,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful tune.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.24,0:14:55.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,What's it called?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.25,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I haven't given it a name.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.25,0:14:59.57,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,It's amazing!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.57,0:15:00.97,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Play it for me again!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.89,0:15:09.18,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But don't tell anyone, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.18,0:15:09.76,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.16,0:17:43.88,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Starting next year, you will be in charge of Plant 3.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.88,0:17:45.67,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Certainly, ma'am.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.38,0:18:17.95,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Ray.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.79,0:18:22.01,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Where did you pick up that tune?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.47,0:18:33.47,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mom.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.90,0:18:36.72,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Why did you give birth to me?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.03,0:18:47.61,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You see, Ray,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.49,0:18:51.09,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I did it to survive,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.87,0:18:53.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,to live longer than the rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.80,0:19:02.92,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,But I suppose this is enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.90,0:19:05.55,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I've finally lost.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.42,0:19:34.77,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.52,0:19:36.86,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Take care on your journey.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.54,0:19:47.84,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I pray that a ray of hope \Nshines at the end of your path.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.36,0:19:55.30,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.18,0:19:58.76,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Rest assured.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.35,0:20:00.93,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,They got out.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.08,0:20:10.44,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.44,0:20:15.50,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.33,0:20:18.95,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,You must've felt so awful in this cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.06,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We did it...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.57,0:20:38.22,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We did it, Norman!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.96,0:20:44.47,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We're out! We got out!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.98,0:20:52.51,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll definitely be back to get everyone else!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.51,0:20:55.40,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This marks our first step...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.90,0:21:15.00,GJM_Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our new dawn.
